tl;dr

botw > genshin, genshin decent tho, gacha = bad and fuck genshin fans no cap, please leave me alone

and also i stopped studying meaning i dont see/hear my cringe classmates anymore, I dont see sum cringe shits saying "omg genshin is so good" or like "omg sir u play genshin!??!!?" while we are having class like fuck off please you ugly model wannabe bitch...

right now im back to playing genshin and im actually enjoying it to the point that im fine spending my money on it, i think whats different now is that it kinda died down a bit and i dont see cringe genshin shit on my feed anymore...
I only quit genshin completely, even tho i played those games at the same time, the only difference is that valorant didnt have the same cancer fanbase as genshin...

I had a classmate that would interrupt my teacher just to ask if he/she played genshin like omfg please. 

I mean sure i played genshin (+valorant) to the point that i got super burnt out but the thing is, I still played valorant from time to time and i didnt quit completely...

when i go on twitter i see sum genshin fan fics or what not even tho i didnt even sign up for that shit, on facebook same shit but like its like omg this genshin character is bla bla, EVEN IN FUCKING ONLINE CLASS...

genshin for me got ruined purely because of the fanbase, I quit the game because of the fanbase, im the type of person that gets annoyed really easily and genshin has one of the most annoying fanbase of anything out there...
another thing that i can give genshin is the music and the lore, both are actually really good and interesting especially the lore...

I think all gacha games are inherently bad when it comes to gameplay, but what i can say about genshin is that, its probably the best gacha game (that i have played) when it comes to gameplay, its actually engaging sometimes and is enjoyable despite the repetitive nature of it...
for the ccp aspect, i dont really care about that as much anymore, i mean i still hate the ccp but like eh, i guess my hate is not as strong as it was before...
also it really annoyed me how people are praising genshin like its a godlike game when its like a subpar botw clone...

back then my main reason (aside from the fanbase) is it being a botw clone and also my hatred of the ccp, both is still there but today i dont rlly mind the botw clone aspect and i think i actually like it now because i think of it as a distraction while i wait for botw2...
i think the main reason why i hate genshin even tho i still play and spend money on it is still the same as my reason a year ago, the fan base.

i survived 2 yrs of not playing gacha games but now Im spending most of my time (and money) on a fucking gacha game and i cant get out bc I have spent money on it already
